<dl id="n54148c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54148c">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54148c"> 148(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> prefigure</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Qu&apos;est-ce que le malade et sa famille attendent du &laquo;docteur&raquo;? Qu&apos;il contraigne le principe malin log&eacute; dans le corps &agrave; en sortir. Ils n&apos;imaginent pas d&apos;autre mani&egrave;re de gu&eacute;rir le malade. Pour parvenir &agrave; ce r&eacute;sultat, le &laquo;docteur&raquo; proc&egrave;de &agrave; une action symbolique. Il <mark>pr&eacute;figure</mark> l&apos;expulsion d&eacute;sir&eacute;e. <br><font color="green">[What does the patient and his family expect from the "doctor"? Let him force the evil principle housed in the body to come out of it. They cannot imagine any other way to cure the patient. To achieve this result, the "doctor" performs a symbolic action. It foreshadows the desired expulsion.]</font> <small> Lucian L&eacute;vy-Bruhl, <a name="LBEM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#LBEM"><cite title="source">L'exp&eacute;rience mystique</cite></a> (1938) 277</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
